==English==

===Etymology===
From [[vinegar]] + [[-y]].

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
# Having the qualities of vinegar; [[acerbic]]; [[bitter]].
#:''Edward's maiden aunt was a '''vinegary''' old soul with a sharp tongue and quick temper; she would ''not'' be receiving a wedding invitation.''
# Of a liquid, having turned partially or fully to vinegar.
#:''When Martha reopened the bottle of wine from last week's party, a '''vinegary''' whiff indicated that drinking was out of the question.''